data.name: XDataInterpreter
desc: offers tooling to interpret different data sources in a structural and chart-type-dependent way.

methods.name: getChartTypeSpecificData
desc: Get chart information that is specific to a particular chart type, by key.

methods.name: interpretDataSource
desc: For standard parameters that may be used, see the service StandardDiagramCreationParameters.

methods.name: isDataCompatible
desc: parses the given data and states, if a reinterpretDataSeries() call can be done without data loss.

methods.name: mergeInterpretedData
desc: Try to reverse the operation done in interpretDataSource().
In case aInterpretedData is the result of interpretDataSource()( xSource ), the result of this method should be xSource.

methods.name: reinterpretDataSeries
desc: Re-interprets the data given in aInterpretedData while keeping the number of data series and the categories.
